## Motivation

The `/ticket-new` skill computes the next ID with a fragile shell pipeline:

```bash
ls tickets/*.erg | sed 's/.*\///' | sort -n | tail -1 | ...
```

A built-in command removes this fragility from every agent's workflow.

## Proposed interface

```
erg next-id tickets/
```

Output: `0019` (the next available 4-digit zero-padded ID).

Scans both `tickets/` and `tickets/archive/` to avoid reusing archived IDs.

## Implementation notes

- Trivial addition to `main.go`: scan filenames, extract max ID, print max+1.
- If no tickets exist, print `0001`.
